#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:5
msgid "Screens"
msgstr "Screen"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:7
msgid ""
"Screens are simply any Widgets created with ``NULL`` passed as parent in "
"the create function. As such, they form the \"root\" of a Widget Tree."
msgstr "Gli Screen sono semplicemente dei Widget creati con ``NULL`` passato come elemento padre nella funzione \"create\". In quanto tali, costituiscono la \"root\" [radice] di un \"Widget Tree\" [Albero dei Widget]."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:10
msgid ""
"Typically the Base Widget is used for this purpose since it has all the "
"features most Screens need. But an :ref:`lv_image` Widget can also be "
"used to create a image as a wallpaper background for the Widget Tree."
msgstr "In genere, a questo scopo viene utilizzato il \"Base Widget\", poiché possiede tutte le funzionalità necessarie alla maggior parte delle schermate. Ma è possibile utilizzare anche un Widget :ref:`lv_image` per creare un'immagine come sfondo per il \"Widget Tree\"."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:17
msgid "Creating Screens"
msgstr "Creazione di Screen"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:19
msgid "Screens are created like this:"
msgstr "Gli Screen vengono creati in questo modo:"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:25
msgid ""
"Screens are created on the :ref:`Default display <default_display>`. As "
"typically there is only one displays the screen are created on them "
"automatically."
msgstr "Gli Screen vengono creati sul :ref:`Display di Default <default_display>`. Poiché in genere è presente un solo display, le schermate vengono create automaticamente."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:28
msgid ""
"The resolution of the screen always matches the resolution of the "
"display. Functions such as :cpp:func:`lv_obj_set_pos` and "
":cpp:func:`lv_obj_set_size` cannot be used on screens."
msgstr "La risoluzione dello schermo corrisponde sempre alla risoluzione del display. Funzioni come :cpp:func:`lv_obj_set_pos` e :cpp:func:`lv_obj_set_size` non possono essere utilizzate sugli Screen."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:32
msgid ""
"The created Screens can be deleted with :cpp:expr:`lv_obj_delete(scr)`, "
"but be sure you do not delete the :ref:`active_screen`."
msgstr "Gli Screen creati possono essere eliminati con :cpp:expr:`lv_obj_delete(scr)`, ma non si deve eliminare lo :ref:`active_screen`."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:40
msgid "Active Screen"
msgstr "Lo Screen Attivo"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:42
msgid ""
"While each :ref:`display` object can have any number of Screen Widgets "
"associated with it, only one of those Screens is considered \"Active\" at"
" any given time. That Screen is referred to as the Display's \"Active "
"Screen\". For this reason, only one Screen and its child Widgets will "
"ever be shown on a display at one time."
msgstr "Sebbene a ogni oggetto :ref:`display` possa essere associato un numero qualsiasi di Widget Screen, solo uno di questi Screen è considerato \"Attivo\" in un dato momento. Quello Screen è definito lo \"Screen Attivo\" del Display. Per questo motivo, su un display verrà visualizzato solo uno Screen e i relativi Widget figli alla volta."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:47
msgid ""
"When each :ref:`display` object was created, a default screen was created"
" with it and set as its \"Active Screen\"."
msgstr "Quando ogni oggetto :ref:`display` è stato creato, è stato creato uno Screen di default con esso e impostato come \"Screen Attivo\"."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:50
msgid ""
"To get a pointer to the \"Active Screen\", call "
":cpp:func:`lv_screen_active`."
msgstr "Per ottenere un puntatore allo \"Screen Attivo\", si chiama :cpp:func:`lv_screen_active`."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:52
msgid ""
"To set a Screen to be the \"Active Screen\", call "
":cpp:func:`lv_screen_load` or :cpp:func:`lv_screen_load_anim`."
msgstr "Per impostare uno Screen come \"Screen Attivo\", si chiama :cpp:func:`lv_screen_load` o :cpp:func:`lv_screen_load_anim`."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:60
msgid "Loading Screens"
msgstr "Caricamento degli Screen"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:62
msgid "To make a screen visible, it needs to be \"loaded\"."
msgstr "Per rendere visibile uno Screen, è necessario \"caricarlo\"."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:64
msgid ""
"The simplest way to load a screen is using "
":cpp:expr:`lv_screen_load(scr1)`. This sets ``scr1`` as the Active "
"Screen."
msgstr "Il modo più semplice per caricare uno Screen è usare :cpp:expr:`lv_screen_load(scr1)`. Questo imposta ``scr1`` come Screen Attivo."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:67
msgid ""
"By using :cpp:expr:`lv_screen_load_anim(scr, transition_type, time, "
"delay, auto_del)` screen loading can be performed"
msgstr "Usando :cpp:expr:`lv_screen_load_anim(scr, transition_type, time, delay, auto_del)`, il caricamento dello Screen può essere eseguito"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:70
msgid "with an optional transition"
msgstr "con una transizione opzionale"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:71
msgid ""
"if ``auto_del`` is ``true`` the previous screen is automatically deleted "
"when any transition animation finishes."
msgstr "se ``auto_del`` è ``true``, lo Screen precedente viene automaticamente eliminata al termine di qualsiasi animazione di transizione."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:74
msgid "The following transition types exist:"
msgstr "Esistono i seguenti tipi di transizione:"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:76
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_NONE`: Switch immediately after "
"``delay`` milliseconds"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_NONE`: Cambia immediatamente dopo ``delay`` millisecondi"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:78
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_LEFT`, "
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_RIGHT`, "
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_TOP` and "
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_BOTTOM`: Move the new screen "
"over the current towards the given direction"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_LEFT`, :cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_RIGHT`, :cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_TOP` e :cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OVER_BOTTOM`: Spostano il nuovo Screen sopra quello corrente verso la direzione indicata"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/screens.rst:83
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OUT_LEFT`, "
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OUT_RIGHT`, "
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OUT_TOP` and "
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_SCREEN_LOAD_ANIM_OUT_BOTTOM`: Move out the old screen"
" over the current towards the given direction"
