msgid ""
"By using :cpp:expr:`lv_obj_bind_style`, it's possible to add a style to a"
" Widget but enable it only if a :ref:`Subject <observer_overview>`'s "
"value is equal to a reference value."
msgstr "Utilizzando :cpp:expr:`lv_obj_bind_style`, è possibile aggiungere uno stile a un Widget, ma abilitarlo solo se il valore di :ref:`Subject <observer_overview>` è uguale a un valore di riferimento."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/styles/style_sheets.rst:170
msgid ""
"It's a great way to implement a light/dark theme switch by normally "
"adding the styles for the light theme, and binding only a few styles for "
"the dark theme to change only a few colors if, e.g., a ``dark_theme`` "
"subject is ``1``."
msgstr "È un ottimo modo per implementare un cambio di tema chiaro/scuro, aggiungendo normalmente gli stili per il tema chiaro e vincolando solo alcuni stili per il tema scuro, in modo da modificare solo pochi colori se, ad esempio, un soggetto ``dark_theme`` è ``1``."

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/styles/themes.rst:5
msgid "Themes"
msgstr "Temi"

#: ../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/common-widget-features/styles/themes.rst:10
msgid ""
"A Theme is a collection of styles with the knowledge of which subset of "
"styles are applied to which types of Widgets. If there is an active theme"
" LVGL applies it to every newly-created widget. This will give a default "
"appearance to the UI which can then be modified by adding further styles."
